Reference

Examination for the Certificate of Proficiency in English (ECPE)

Data on ECPE grammar from Templin and Hoffman (2013) and Templin and Bradshaw (2014) used in Culpepper and Chen (2019).

items_ecpe

Examination for the Certificate of Proficiency in English (ECPE) Item Responses

qmatrix_ecpe

Examination for the Certificate of Proficiency in English (ECPE) Expert-Derived Q matrix

Fraction Addition and Subtraction

Data exploring errors in Fraction Addition and Subtraction Problems from Tatsuoka, C. (2002) generated in Tatsuoka, K. K. (1984) used in Chen et al. (2021), Chen et al. (2020), Culpepper (2019a), Culpepper and Chen (2019), and Chen et al. (2018)

items_fractions

Fraction Subtraction and Addition Assessment Item Responses

qmatrix_fractions

Fraction Subtraction and Addition Assessment Expert-Derived Q Matrix

Elementary Probability Theory Assessment

Data from an Elementary Probability Theory Assessment by Heller, J., & Wickelmaier, F. (2013) used in Chen et al. (2021)

items_probability_part_one_full items_probability_part_one_reduced

Elementary Probability Theory Assessment Item Responses

qmatrix_probability_part_one

Elementary Probability Theory Assessment Expert-Derived Q Matrix

Calculus-based probability and statistics homework

Data from a calculus-based probability and statistics course homework assignment.

items_ordered_pswc_hw

Calculus-based probability and statistics course homework problems

Human Connectome Project’s Penn Progressive Matrices Fluid Intelligence Assessment

Data collected by the Human Connectome Project using the a reduced set of Raven’s Progressive Matrices known as the Penn Progressive Matrices.

items_hcp_penn_matrix items_hcp_penn_matrix_missing

Human Connectome Project's Penn Progressive Matrices Fluid Intelligence Assessment

Revised Purdue Spatial Visualization Test: Visualization of Rotations (Revised PSVT:R)

Data collected using Revised PSVT:R by Yoon (2011) from Culpepper and Balamuta (2017) used in Culpepper (2015) and Culpepper and Balamuta (2017)

items_revised_psvtr

Revised PSVT:R Item Responses

Early Childhood Longitudinal Study, Kindergarten Approaches to Learning (ECLS-K ATL)

Data in the Early Childhood Longitudinal Study, Kindergarten (ECLS-K) Approaches to Learning survey by NCES (2011) used in Culpepper (2019b).

Subset of Early Childhood Longitudinal Study, Kindergarten (ECLS-K)'s Approaches to Learning Item Responses

Data in the Trends in International Mathematics and Science Study 2015 (TIMSS) Grade 8 Student Background Survey by TIMSS 2015.

OpenPsychometrics

Data sets compiled from OpenPsychometrics’ raw data portal. These data sets have been processed to meet definitions for use in psychometric applications. Most notably, any observations with missing data have been removed and responses have been converted to a correct/incorrect marking for the items matrix. Matrix reasoning was used in Chen et al. (2020).
